ecHqtApYRnRVQ5Zd","target":"recEOMPybxT6g8y8E","label":"event"},{"source":"recHqtApYRnRVQ5Zd","target":"recKk6oSdN570sACg","label":"event"},{"source":"recHqtApYRnRVQ5Zd","target":"recuwnodcdBQpgk6J","label":"event"},{"source":"recHqtApYRnRVQ5Zd","target":"recQRI9PzXBoW4QVD","label":"event"},{"source":"recHqtApYRnRVQ5Zd","target":"recUQaOuprbt82K3O","label":"event"}],"verses":[{"id":"recgw8qkMulCopTmz","ref":"2Kgs.15.1","text":"In the twenty and seventh year of Jeroboam king of Israel began Azariah son of Amaziah king of Judah to reign.","year":-810},{"id":"recMQfljHGaNc19HF","ref":"2Kgs.15.2","text":"Sixteen years old was he when he began to reign, and he reigned two and fifty years in Jerusalem. And his mother’s name was Jecholiah of Jerusalem.","year":-810},{"id":"recylul7eOGkKySPM","ref":"2Kgs.15.3","text":"And he did that which was right in the sight of the LORD, according to all that his father Amaziah had done;","year":-810},{"id":"recfONdMFISt9sCiv","ref":"2Kgs.15.4","text":"Save that the high places were not removed: the people sacrificed and burnt incense still on the high places.","year":-810},{"id":"reccR17ek6zwvfrIg","ref":"2Kgs.15.5","text":"And the LORD smote the king, so that he was a leper unto the day of his death, and dwelt in a several house. And Jotham the king’s son was over the house, judging the people of the land.","year":-765},{"id":"recjQ580ve16JIjlQ","ref":"2Kgs.15.6","text":"And the rest of the acts of Azariah, and all that he did, are they not written in the book of the chronicles of the kings of Judah?","year":-765},{"id":"recVKPGdRooFXrSpj","ref":"2Kgs.15.7","text":"So Azariah slept with his fathers; and they buried him with his fathers in the city of David: and Jotham his son reigned in his stead.","year":-758},{"id":"recqYG33vkvSdmFuJ","ref":"2Kgs.15.8","text":"In the thirty and eighth year of Azariah king of Judah did Zachariah the son of Jeroboam reign over Israel in Samaria six months.","year":-773}]}
